			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I can't see any reason why not both our charm and Mez should be capped at equal level to enchanter.
<br />

<br />
* Our charm/mez is only working on Elementals.
<br />

<br />
* Our tradeoff for having a charmed pet is slightly bigger. We can't have our "powerful" mage pet up while we have a charmed pet. Enchanters sacrifice their (according to them) gimp animation. Mages sacrifice their ONLY form of defense.
<br />

<br />
* We don't have Total Domination 3, Runes, Stuns, and other useful tools for dealing with charmed pet.
<br />

<br />
* Speaking against that we should have equal cap is the fact that we have a better pet haste buff (85% instead of 70%), but then again - we don't have slow like they do and 70% slow makes a bigger difference than any combination of haste+overhaste in the game.
<br />

<br />
Would be nice if Rytan or anyone in the Dev team could explain what they were thinking when they added the cap to Mage charm/mez.
<br />

<br />
Would it make us overpowered? Then what is Enchanters?</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
