			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">As its been pointed out, I wholeheartedly support raising the levels on mez and charm. Our ability to mez and charm reliably is already heavily handicapped by the following factors:
<br />

<br />
1) No memblur, snare, or root to keep the mob from coming after you
<br />
2) No rune, stun, or slow to protect you when it gets to you.
<br />
3) No healing/ lifetap / regen spells in case you do get hit.
<br />
4) No AA's or items to increase the duration of these abilities
<br />
5) A rediculously small number of summoned creatures in game
<br />
6) The low level caps on the spell make its usefulness spotty at best, certainly not an ability that can truely be "relied upon"
<br />

<br />
The abilities in their present form are little more than a tease. Raise the level cap, add summoned mobs in more zones, and give mages a single defensive spell, and I think it would be an appropriate adjustment.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=381929&resize=true" target="_blank" class="postlink">Naladini Dreamfyre</a>
<br />
Arch Mage of 62 Seasons - <a href="http://www.stormhammer.org/forums" target="_blank" class="postlink">Stormhammer</a>
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Magician pets are not strong enough to justify our lack of a defensive spell</span></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
